      <hedline>
        <hl1>Kennedy's Mathis Picks Virginia</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By BRANDON LILLY</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Lilly, Brandon</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>High school basketball player J C Mathis to play basketball at University of Virginia (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>J. C. Mathis, who helped lead John F. Kennedy High School to the Public Schools Athletic League championship this season, will play at the University of Virginia, the 6-foot-9-inch forward announced yesterday at a news conference.</p>
        <p>Mathis cited Virginia's tough academic standards as well as a chance to play in the Atlantic Coast Conference as the reasons for his decision.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>J. C. Mathis, who helped lead John F. Kennedy High School to the Public Schools Athletic League championship this season, will play at the University of Virginia, the 6-foot-9-inch forward announced yesterday at a news conference.</p>
        <p>Mathis cited Virginia's tough academic standards as well as a chance to play in the Atlantic Coast Conference as the reasons for his decision.</p>
        <p>Mathis averaged 17.2 points and 10.5 rebounds a game last season in leading Kennedy to the city title. The Knights finished the season 28-3.</p>
        <p>BRANDON LILLY</p>
        <p>PLUS: BASKETBALL</p>
